    </p>
    <p>
        ğŸ”¹ We can thereby clearly calculate the surface area by finding the area of each faces and add them all together to get the surface area of the Prism.
    </p>
    <p>
       ğŸ”¹ For example, If we are given a cylinder, the top and bottom faces are circles and the curved area is like a rectangle. So when finding it's surface area we find the area of the two circles and the area of the rectangle then we dd all these areas al together to compute yhe cylinder's surface area.
    </p>
